h channel, and a 2.5d longer ocean passage dragging the TCE down. Of the 10.2 days longer voyage we could invoice 2.5 days as demurrage. A part from the bad weather, no major operational issues in port. Captain very alert and responsive on the sudden change of rotation last minute."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-29T22:38:39.687","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"october Urea consumption \u002B neste equipment added"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-09T08:11:35.28","modifiedByFull":"Bergh, Oliver","remark":"Rough weather during laden leg prolonged the voyage by 2,5 days and reduced the PnL with $91k. New PnL: $127,897"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-07T08:35:29.557","modifiedByFull":"Bergh, Oliver","remark":"Discharge orders received - Discharge at three port instead of 1. Freight and port costs updated accordingly, new PnL: $121,566"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-02T12:29:08.71","modifiedByFull":"Bergh, Oliver","remark":"Overage of 933.600 MT added"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-11-01T10:58:58.4","modifiedByFull":"Bergh, Oliver","remark":"Updated hire which changed from 32k to 28k pdpr on Oct 30th."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-10-25T12:28:21.95","modifiedByFull":"Bergh, Oliver","remark":"Weather prevented bunkers to be delivered at Skaw, and Pilot couldn\u0027t stay onboard during bunker ops and disembark at Skaw. Vsl was STRONGLY advised to keep the pilot onboard until Skaw hence pilot wasn\u0027t dropped just after Great Belt. So vsl had to first go to Skaw to drop Pilot, then return to Gbg for bunkers...."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-10-23T10:00:48.403","modifiedByFull":"Bergh, Oliver","remark":"Bunker stem inserted off Gothenburg dragging down TCE. New PnL $102,247"}],"offhireList":[{"id":196521,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":227877,"gradeName":"LSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}